page.title: 10WICKLEWOOD WALK PART 1
page.content: I begin at High Oak. From here I can see most of Wicklewood. There is a garage, a few houses and a water pumping station.Descending I pass a pond,a farm and cottages. This is the Green. Along Hackford Road I come to the Cherry Tree public house. Turning left into High Street I go downhill passing the Village Hall,village shop and our famous windmill. Further down is a disused Primative Methodist chapel and an old cottage that used to be the post office.Modern houses and bungalows line this road.Near the bottom of High Street is a cross-roads.To the right is Low Street with some old people's homes. On one corner is an old house that once was the Kimberley Arms public house, for the Kimberley estate owned much of Wicklewood.
